##Number said Epidemic 0223: Beijing yesterday the first zero new! Outbreak contained outside Hubei

I-CAIJING

CAIJING magazine official Wechat. "CAIJING" magazine, sponsored by the China Securities Market Research Center, was first published in 1998, adhering to the news concept of "independence, exclusiveness and originality" , and is known for authoritative, impartial and professional reporting, it is a must-read publication for policy-makers, researchers and managers in the field of politics and economics.

Twenty-one provinces in the country on the 22nd, zero new, continue to consolidate the results of the war against the epidemic. The latest data confirm our previous prediction that the suspected case stock in Hubei will begin to decline on the 22nd after the success of the dragnet investigation

By Xu Jin, data researcher, Caijing

Image | CAIJING visual center

Editor | Sheryl Rong

1. Cumulative confirmed cases: the total number of new pneumonia cases in China is expected to be controlled at 80,000

As of 24:00 on February 22,76,936 cases of new coronary pneumonia had been confirmed in China. The following is a regional trend map.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Figure 1.1

The Red and black lines show that we are in a race with death!

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Figure 1.2

The top of trend line outside Wuhan has been clear, it can be seen that the cumulative cases in non-hubei areas will stay at about 13,000, Hubei non-wuhan areas will be about 19,000, Wuhan will be about 48,000. The main variable is whether this new pneumonia will leave no long tail, as SARS did, or whether it will drag out a long tail, as the exponential function shows (some experts worry recently) ? Or somewhere in between? To wait for non-hubei area data to confirm.

Two, new cases: Beijing Welcomes Zero new cases! All non-hubei regions closed

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Figure 2

The number of new cases in non-hubei areas further decreased to 18 cases, with an average of 0.6 cases per province. Zero new provinces and Cities 21, Beijing ushered in the outbreak of the first "zero new. ".

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Figure 3

Hubei Statistical Caliber Adjustment Today, in the original 18 cities outside the new list of prisons. It is not clear whether the data will be expanded or reclassified, and its impact on data trends remains to be seen. Our guess is that it has just been included in the statistics because of the further strengthening of the territorial management principle of epidemic prevention. But in any case, the data release itself is particularly laudable! In the face of the epidemic, the public would like to see a firm and self-confident government. According to yesterday's situation, the number of new cases in the prison is close to Wuhan, more than other cities and states in Hubei. The outbreak in the prison is unfortunate and is believed to be under control. Overall, there is no change in the assessment of Hubei's positive trend.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Figure 4

New cases have picked up in Wuhan. Combined with the new data of suspected, suspected excluded and suspected isolated in Hubei, the analysis shows that this is mainly influenced by the measures of pulling net screening and speeding up the detection speed to promote "daily clearance zero" rather than the rebound of the epidemic situation. Do not change the judgment that a positive reversal has taken place in the war situation in Wuhan.

3. INCREASE RATE OF CONFIRMED CASES: the growth rate of non-hubei area "tends to zero" , Hubei and Wuhan pick up slightly, but do not change the trend judgment

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Figure 5

The growth rate of non-hubei region in China has dropped to 0.18% , which has reached "zero" in statistical sense. Hubei and Wuhan rose slightly, there are dragnet inspection to speed up the promotion of "daily Clearance Zero" factor, but also does not rule out data adjustment factors. Do not change the original good trend judgment.

Contact Tracing: Tracking in Hubei and Wuhan has been strengthened

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Figure 6

Hubei this indicator continues to climb! The recent three-day moving average shows a strong upward trend: The tracking ratio has further increased to about 20. It was reported that on the evening of February 21, when Ying Yong, the party secretary of Hubei Province, was addressing the deployment of the main battlefield in Wuhan, he clearly pointed out that "we should further strengthen the flow modulation, strengthen the construction of the flow modulation team and big data analysis, and improve the closed loop of work (flow modulation-isolation-screening-treatment-flow modulation) " , "where conditions permit, all close contacts in Wuhan shall be isolated. " . It is encouraging that this will completely block the spread of infection.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Figure 7

Both Hubei and non-hubei areas continue to decline, meaning more medical resources, social human resources and isolation space can be released into the new close contact tracking isolation.

Suspected Cases: the increase in decline, Hubei stock after the network screening operation also declined

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Figure 8

Additional suspected cases in Hubei (including Wuhan) continued downward, confirming Wuhan's "five percent" success.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Figure 9

Previously, we predicted that Hubei will start to decline today after the success of grid search, and today it is true! Confirm the result of "pulling net to screen" .

6. Hospital admissions: Hubei, Africa, and Hubei are all down. The number of people diagnosed as not being hospitalized in Hubei has also dropped

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
10

The number of people being treated in the hospital declined and beds continued to be released. Our guess is that the number of people in Hubei who have been diagnosed and have not been hospitalized has also decreased.

Mortality Rate, cure rate

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Figure 11

The case-fatality rate has risen for more than two weeks and is expected to continue. There are the time of death and the newly confirmed increase of factors out of SYNC (non-hubei) , there are also the factors of treatment capacity and medical resources (Wuhan) .

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
12

The cure rate is rising even faster. Let's race against death!

8. New discharge and new diagnoses

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Figure 13.1 number of newly discharged and newly diagnosed cases

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Figure 13.2

Core medical resources continue to be released.

Summary: Hubei and Wuhan continue their positive trend. The spread of the epidemic in non-hubei areas of China has been contained. The number of new cases has reached zero in a statistical sense. Statistically, there was no evidence of a resurgence of the epidemic, nor was there any case that suggested a resurgence. Continue to appeal to areas outside Hubei in the prevention and control awareness under the premise of non-lax, to speed up the orderly resumption of production.
